Package: lindia
Title: Linear Regression Diagonostic Plots in GGPlot
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(person("Yeuk Yu", "Lee", email = "lyeukyu@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
	person("Samuel", "Ventura", email = "sventura@stat.cmu.edu",
		role = c("aut")))
Description: Allows easy generation of linear regression diagnostic plots in
    GGPlot. Graph types include residual plots, QQPlot, Boxcox graph, scale-location plot, and residual leverage plot. This package is meant for easy scheming of linear regression diagnostics. See the ggplot2 websites for more information regarding the functionality of how ggplot works.
Depends:
    R (>= 3.2.2)
License: What license is it under?
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 5.0.1
Imports:
	ggplot2,
	gridExtra
Suggests: testthat
